snippet.title: Moving Back to the White House - Barron Trump Sings
snippet.description:
Moving Back to the White House

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics
[Verse 1]
Boxes packed, we’re on the move,
History calling, nothing to prove.
I walk the halls I once knew well,
Stories in the walls, they’ve got more to tell.

[Pre-Chorus]
From the front gates to the West Wing glow,
It feels like home, yeah, I already know.

[Chorus]
I’m moving back into the White House,
With Mom and Dad, the lights don’t go out.
Dreams are big where the flags still wave,
In the land of the free, and the home of the brave.
I’m moving back into the White House,
A chapter turns, and I’ll stand proud.

[Verse 2]
Mom walks strong with her quiet grace,
Dad’s got fire you can’t replace.
And I’m just here, watching it unfold,
Living through a story that’s yet untold.

[Pre-Chorus]
Echoes of history in every room,
From the Rose Garden blooms to the Lincoln gloom.

[Chorus]
I’m moving back into the White House,
With Mom and Dad, the lights don’t go out.
Dreams are big where the flags still wave,
In the land of the free, and the home of the brave.
I’m moving back into the White House,
A chapter turns, and I’ll stand proud.

[Bridge]
Some call it power, some call it fame,
But to me, it’s just home by another name.
Through the storms and the cheers outside the gate,
We’ll rise together, it’s never too late.

[Final Chorus]
I’m moving back into the White House,
With Mom and Dad, the lights don’t go out.
Dreams are big where the flags still wave,
In the land of the free, and the home of the brave.
Yeah, I’m moving back into the White House,
Writing tomorrow from here and now.

[Outro]
Back to the White House…
With my mom and dad,
It’s the life I have,
And I’ll stand proud.
